exercises.description: Hinge at hips and swing the kettlebell between legs to chest or eye level, building explosive hip power. Switch hand at the top of the swing.

exercises.name: Single Kettlebell Clean & Press to Pause Windmill
exercises.description: A complex movement that combines a single kettlebell clean and press followed by a controlled windmill with a pause.
exercises.notes: This exercise challenges stability, mobility, and strength simultaneously.

exercises.name: Single Kettlebell Clean and Press
exercises.description: A dynamic full-body movement to build strength, power, and coordination.

exercises.name: Single Kettlebell Figure Eight
exercises.description: Passing the kettlebell between the legs in a figure-eight pattern, enhancing coordination and grip.

exercises.name: Single Kettlebell Front Squat
exercises.description: Hold the kettlebell at chest level and perform a squat to target quads, glutes, and core stability.

exercises.name: Single Kettlebell High Pull
exercises.description: A powerful movement pulling the kettlebell to chest level, engaging the back and shoulders.

exercises.name: Single Kettlebell Jerk
exercises.description: An overhead press with a dip and drive movement, improving explosive shoulder power.

exercises.name: Single Kettlebell Overhead Lunge
exercises.description: Hold one kettlebell overhead in one hand and perform lunges to challenge stability and core control.

exercises.name: Single Kettlebell Overhead Press
exercises.description: Press the kettlebell overhead, focusing on shoulder stability and core engagement.

exercises.name: Single Kettlebell Russian Twist
exercises.description: Sit on the floor, lean back slightly, and twist the kettlebell side to side for oblique engagement.

exercises.name: Single Kettlebell Swing
exercises.description: Hinge at hips and swing the kettlebell between legs to chest or eye level, building explosive hip power.

exercises.name: Single Kettlebell Swing
exercises.description: Hinge at hips and swing the kettlebell between legs to chest or eye level, building explosive hip power.

exercises.name: Single Kettlebell Windmill
exercises.description: Hold the kettlebell overhead and hinge at the hips to touch the opposite foot, improving mobility and core strength.

exercises.name: Single Leg Stance (Balance)
exercises.description: A fundamental proprioceptive exercise to improve balance, ankle stability, and hip control. It retrains the body's ability to stabilize on one leg.
exercises.notes: Stand on one leg, keeping your pelvis level and your standing knee slightly bent. Try to hold for 30 seconds. To make it harder, close your eyes or stand on an unstable surface like a pillow.

exercises.name: Skater Jumps
exercises.description: A lateral plyometric exercise that targets legs and improves agility.

exercises.name: Sled Pull
exercises.description: A full-body strength and conditioning exercise involving pulling a weighted sled using straps or a harness.

exercises.name: Sled Push
exercises.description: A full-body strength and conditioning exercise involving pushing a weighted sled.

exercises.name: Slow Eccentric Floor Skullcrusher
exercises.description: A slow controlled tricep isolation exercise performed lying on the floor, lowering one or two kettlebells towards the forehead.

exercises.name: Slow Eccentric Floor Skullcrusher to Close Grip Floor Press
exercises.description: A combination of a slow eccentric skullcrusher directly into a close grip floor press, targeting the triceps.

exercises.name: Slow Eccentric Pause Towel Curls
exercises.description: A bicep curl variation using a towel looped through a kettlebell handle to challenge grip strength and target the biceps differently.

exercises.name: Stair Climbing
exercises.description: A vigorous cardiovascular exercise that targets the glutes, quads, and hamstrings.

exercises.name: Standing Calf Raise
exercises.description: An isolation exercise for the calf muscles (gastrocnemius and soleus), typically performed on a machine or with free weights.

exercises.name: Straight Bar Dip
exercises.description: An exercise that targets the chest, triceps, and shoulders by lowering and pressing on a straight bar or dip station.

exercises.name: Straight Leg Raise
exercises.description: A basic strengthening exercise for the quadriceps and hip flexors that can be performed without bending a potentially injured or painful knee.
exercises.notes: Lie on your back with one leg straight and the other knee bent. Tighten the thigh muscle of the straight leg and slowly lift it 6-12 inches off the floor, keeping the leg straight. Lower slowly.

exercises.name: Suitcase Deadlift to Anti-Rotation Row
exercises.description: A combination exercise starting with a suitcase deadlift, followed by a row that challenges anti-rotation core strength.

exercises.name: Superman
exercises.description: A bodyweight exercise that strengthens the lower back, glutes, and hamstrings by simultaneously lifting arms and legs off the floor while lying prone.

exercises.name: Superman
exercises.description: A lower back and posterior chain exercise performed lying prone, lifting arms and legs simultaneously.

exercises.name: Superman Extensions
exercises.description: Lying prone, lift arms, chest, and legs off the ground to strengthen lower back and posterior chain.

exercises.name: Terminal Knee Extension (TKE)
exercises.description: An exercise that isolates and strengthens the vastus medialis oblique (VMO), a key quadriceps muscle for knee stability and proper patellar tracking.
exercises.notes: Anchor a resistance band behind you at knee height. Step into the band with one leg and step forward to create tension. Start with the knee slightly bent and then straighten it by squeezing your quadriceps. Control the return.

exercises.name: Tire Flip
exercises.description: A powerful full-body exercise common in strongman training, involving flipping a large tire.

exercises.name: Towel Scrunches
exercises.description: An exercise to strengthen the intrinsic muscles of the foot, which can help with conditions like plantar fasciitis and improve arch support.
exercises.notes: Sit in a chair with your bare foot flat on a towel. Use your toes to scrunch the towel towards you. Repeat until you've pulled the entire towel in, then push it back out and start again.

exercises.name: Triceps Stretch (Overhead)
exercises.description: A static stretch for the triceps, performed by reaching one arm overhead and bending the elbow.

exercises.name: Tuck Planche
exercises.description: An advanced balance move where knees are tucked in, challenging core and shoulder stability.

exercises.name: Turkish Get-Up (TGU)
exercises.description: A complex, full-body exercise involving transitioning from lying on the floor to standing, all while holding a kettlebell (or dumbbell) overhead. Enhances stability, mobility, and strength.

exercises.name: Twist Sit-up
exercises.description: A core exercise that combines a traditional sit-up with a torso twist to engage the obliques and rectus abdominis.
exercises.notes: As you sit up, twist your torso to bring your opposite elbow towards your knee.

exercises.name: Upper Trapezius Stretch
exercises.description: A stretch to relieve tension and tightness in the upper trapezius muscle, which runs from the neck to the shoulder. Commonly tight in individuals with neck pain or headaches.
exercises.notes: Sit in a chair and gently tilt your head to one side as if trying to touch your ear to your shoulder. For a deeper stretch, you can gently hold the side of your head with your hand or hold onto the chair with the opposite hand.

exercises.name: ViPR Cylinder Drop Squat
exercises.description: An exercise that challenges reactive strength and proper squatting mechanics by dropping the ViPR from an overhead position and catching it in a deep squat.

exercises.name: ViPR Cylinder Lift
exercises.description: A full-body loaded movement that mimics lifting an object from the ground to an overhead position, integrating the lower body, core, and upper body.

exercises.name: ViPR Ice Skater
exercises.description: A plyometric exercise mimicking the motion of ice skating, where you bound from side to side while swinging the ViPR, developing lateral power and agility.

exercises.name: ViPR Lateral Shift with Rip
exercises.description: A dynamic, full-body movement combining a lateral lunge (shift) with a powerful push-pull (rip) of the ViPR, building strength and coordination in the frontal plane.

exercises.name: ViPR Shoveling
exercises.description: A functional movement that mimics the action of shoveling, developing power in a diagonal, rotational pattern across the body.

exercises.name: ViPR Thread the Needle
exercises.description: A rotational core exercise where the ViPR is passed through the legs in a lunge or squat position, enhancing rotational strength and hip mobility.

exercises.name: Wall Handstand
exercises.description: A balance and shoulder stability exercise performed against a wall, building strength for free-standing handstands.

exercises.name: Wall Push-up
exercises.description: An introductory push-up variation that reduces the load on the shoulders, wrists, and chest. It's an excellent way to begin rebuilding upper body strength safely.
exercises.notes: Stand facing a wall, a little more than arm's length away. Place your hands on the wall and slowly bend your elbows to bring your chest towards the wall. Keep your core engaged and body in a straight line.

exercises.name: Wall Sit
exercises.description: An isometric hold that targets the quadriceps, glutes, and calves, simulating a seated position against a wall.

exercises.name: Wall Sit (Isometric)
exercises.description: An isometric exercise to build endurance in the quadriceps, glutes, and hamstrings without requiring movement through a painful range of motion.
exercises.notes: Lean your back against a wall and slide down until your knees are bent at a 45 to 90-degree angle, as if sitting in a chair. Hold the position for a prescribed amount of time. Ensure your knees stay aligned over your ankles.
